Dia. 03 Vital Point of Death
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par If it is so then it is easy to think that Black 1 is the vital point.
\par In the previous diagrams, this move saved or killed Black.
\par
\par However if Black plays at 1, White's placement at 2 is the \cf1\b vital point of death\cf0\b0 .
\par If Black plays at 3, White captures with 4.
\par
\par
\par }
